Aqua America Inc. (WTR) , the second-largest
U.S. water utility by market value, bought a community water
system in Pennsylvania for $3.4 million.  The utility purchased the water assets from Bristol
Township, about 20 miles (32 kilometers) northeast of
Philadelphia, Aqua America said today in a statement. The system
serves about 1,300 residents and 175 businesses.  The acquisition is  Bryn Mawr , Pennsylvania-based Aqua
